286
00:17:06,160 --> 00:17:08,720
No, no. Nothing but my gay intuition.

287
00:17:08,799 --> 00:17:12,160
I promise.
We're totally platonic, good friends.

288
00:17:12,240 --> 00:17:14,960
Disappointing, but… Okay.

289
00:17:15,039 --> 00:17:16,319
You all right, Nick?

290
00:17:21,720 --> 00:17:24,039
Oi, Nick! Come, come.

291
00:17:25,279 --> 00:17:26,319
Join in, yeah?

292
00:17:34,079 --> 00:17:35,079
Quick question.

293
00:17:36,000 --> 00:17:38,359
Why are the other team literal adult men?

294
00:17:39,319 --> 00:17:41,119
They're a specialist sports school.

295
00:17:41,200 --> 00:17:42,279
[Elle] Oh, wow.

296
00:17:42,880 --> 00:17:43,880
Oh, God.

297
00:17:49,680 --> 00:17:50,519
Sorry.

298
00:17:51,079 --> 00:17:51,920
Nervous.

299
00:17:54,200 --> 00:17:56,559
[captain] Be dominant.
We have to show them who we are,

300
00:17:56,640 --> 00:17:59,079
what we're proud of, yeah, boys?
One, two, three!

301
00:17:59,160 --> 00:18:01,279
-[all yell]
-[blows whistle]

302
00:18:01,359 --> 00:18:02,440
[Nick] Come on, boys.

303
00:18:02,519 --> 00:18:04,480
[cheering]

304
00:18:06,240 --> 00:18:07,519
All right, line up, boys.

305
00:18:15,960 --> 00:18:16,880
Come on, Nicholas!

306
00:18:16,960 --> 00:18:18,559
Harry, don't let the game go soft.

307
00:18:22,680 --> 00:18:26,640
So, does anyone remember
the rules of rugby because I don't.

308
00:18:26,720 --> 00:18:27,920
-[girls] No.
-Yeah.

309
00:18:28,720 --> 00:18:30,119
Come on, Nicholas!

310
00:18:31,920 --> 00:18:32,839
[all grunt]

311
00:18:33,359 --> 00:18:34,319
Ooh.

312
00:18:36,839 --> 00:18:38,440
[grunting]

313
00:18:47,599 --> 00:18:49,599
[crowd cheering]

314
00:18:49,680 --> 00:18:51,400
Come on. Let's go, boys. Come on!

315
00:18:52,240 --> 00:18:53,079
Head up!

316
00:18:53,160 --> 00:18:55,200
-[thunder rumbling]
-[all groaning]

317
00:18:57,599 --> 00:18:59,160
There we are, yeah.

318
00:18:59,240 --> 00:19:01,640
[St. John's boys] Five, six, seven. Heave!

319
00:19:10,680 --> 00:19:12,079
-[Charlie grunts]
-Charlie!

320
00:19:13,079 --> 00:19:14,599
-Ow.
-Oh, my gosh.

321
00:19:16,359 --> 00:19:18,079
[coach] Get back up, Charlie.

322
00:19:18,160 --> 00:19:19,279
Yes, Charlie!

323
00:19:19,359 --> 00:19:21,720
-Shake it off, it's fine! Come on!
-Yes!

324
00:19:22,400 --> 00:19:23,279
Hold it.

325
00:19:30,920 --> 00:19:33,519
-[cheering]
-[whistle blows]

326
00:19:41,599 --> 00:19:43,799
Mate. See that number 14, yeah?

327
00:19:43,880 --> 00:19:46,160
He definitely has something for you, mate.

328
00:19:46,240 --> 00:19:48,039
A crush or something, mate.

329
00:19:48,119 --> 00:19:50,000
[Tao] Is Harry Green picking on Charlie?

330
00:19:50,079 --> 00:19:51,440
[Elle] Maybe they're friends.

331
00:19:51,519 --> 00:19:52,599
[Tao] That's even worse.

332
00:19:53,359 --> 00:19:56,000
Next, Charlie will be bringing
the whole rugby team

333
00:19:56,079 --> 00:19:59,720
to our film night
and making us watch Avengers or something.

334
00:19:59,799 --> 00:20:01,680
Is that your nightmare scenario?

335
00:20:01,759 --> 00:20:04,920
Watching a movie you hate
with people you don't like very much?

336
00:20:05,000 --> 00:20:08,119
Charlie's befriending bullies,
and our friendship group is falling apart.

337
00:20:08,200 --> 00:20:09,880
-Take this seriously.
-Hey.

338
00:20:09,960 --> 00:20:13,200
I didn't come to risk seeing
all the Truham Boys who used to pick on me

339
00:20:13,279 --> 00:20:16,319
just for you to tell me
our friendship group's falling apart.

340
00:20:17,400 --> 00:20:20,680
Go after him, mate. 100%.

341
00:20:22,039 --> 00:20:23,960
All right. Boys, set up. Set up.

342
00:20:24,920 --> 00:20:25,799
Go on, mate.

343
00:20:26,799 --> 00:20:28,319
Keep your head up, Charlie.

344
00:20:28,400 --> 00:20:30,200
-[coach] Hang in there, boys.
-[Nick] Come on!

345
00:20:31,240 --> 00:20:32,640
[thunder rumbling]

346
00:20:41,799 --> 00:20:43,759
[breathing heavily]

347
00:20:49,000 --> 00:20:50,240
[Charlie grunts]

348
00:20:50,319 --> 00:20:52,319
-Charlie!
-[whistle blows]

349
00:21:01,880 --> 00:21:04,039
[Nick] Is it okay if we, like…

350
00:21:06,200 --> 00:21:07,160
Keep this a secret?

351
00:21:09,240 --> 00:21:10,079
[Nick] Yeah.

352
00:21:11,799 --> 00:21:16,160
[coach] Okay, that's it, I'm calling it.
This rain is too dangerous!

353
00:21:16,240 --> 00:21:20,000
Match is over! Everyone off the pitch!

354
00:21:20,079 --> 00:21:21,119
[breathing heavily]

355
00:21:32,039 --> 00:21:32,920
[knock at door]

356
00:21:36,079 --> 00:21:36,920
Hey.

357
00:21:37,680 --> 00:21:38,559
Hey.

358
00:21:41,079 --> 00:21:42,480
Is your nose okay?

359
00:21:42,559 --> 00:21:43,400
I don't know.

360
00:21:45,519 --> 00:21:46,559
Let me see.

361
00:21:56,039 --> 00:21:57,079
It looks fine.

362
00:21:57,759 --> 00:21:58,640
Cool.

363
00:21:59,920 --> 00:22:01,920
You've got some mud on your face though.

364
00:22:08,599 --> 00:22:10,440
[soft music playing]

365
00:22:17,079 --> 00:22:18,680
Um, sorry… [chuckles nervously]

366
00:22:20,000 --> 00:22:20,839
What?

367
00:22:20,920 --> 00:22:23,440
I'm really sorry
for being all clingy and annoying.

368
00:22:23,920 --> 00:22:25,799
I'm making this so awkward.

369
00:22:25,880 --> 00:22:28,519
You wanted to keep us a secret
and I'm messing it up.

370
00:22:30,240 --> 00:22:32,440
I'm the one who should be saying sorry.

371
00:22:37,400 --> 00:22:39,160
[Isaac] Uh…

372
00:22:39,240 --> 00:22:40,079
Sorry…

373
00:22:40,759 --> 00:22:41,640
for, um…

374
00:22:43,000 --> 00:22:48,720
interrupting, but Ms. Singh told me
to give you some… antiseptic wipes.

375
00:22:51,000 --> 00:22:51,920
Okay.

376
00:22:52,000 --> 00:22:54,400
[door opens and closes]

377
00:22:57,160 --> 00:22:58,640
Um… [clears throat]

378
00:23:00,319 --> 00:23:01,319
I'd better go.

379
00:23:02,000 --> 00:23:02,880
Okay.

380
00:23:05,880 --> 00:23:07,160
Isaac won't say anything.

381
00:23:10,039 --> 00:23:10,880
Yeah.

382
00:23:12,400 --> 00:23:13,240
Okay.

383
00:23:16,160 --> 00:23:17,160
[door closes]

384
00:23:21,799 --> 00:23:24,480
Charlie's not going to give up
on Nick Nelson, is he?

385
00:23:25,160 --> 00:23:26,440
Highly doubt it.

386
00:23:26,519 --> 00:23:27,480
[scoffs]

387
00:23:28,880 --> 00:23:31,039
Maybe we should
just stop getting involved.

388
00:23:32,480 --> 00:23:35,440
I can't believe
you just actually suggested that.

389
00:23:35,519 --> 00:23:39,160
You, Tao Xu,
King of Getting Involved. [giggles]

390
00:23:39,240 --> 00:23:40,400
Shut up.

391
00:23:40,960 --> 00:23:43,039
-It was nice meeting your friends though.
-Yeah?

392
00:23:43,119 --> 00:23:44,319
Yeah.

393
00:23:44,400 --> 00:23:45,559
They seem cool.

394
00:23:45,640 --> 00:23:46,519
They are.

395
00:23:47,839 --> 00:23:48,960
